//podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/2-biotech-bro-agustin-zavala-on-biotech-investing-starting/id1532246931?i=1000492652978"><strong>Apple Podcasts</strong></a></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Listen on </strong><a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/69xEl8wZC8Gc6FrI5yUxQO?si=KEO9y5gETh-XfSTwMzKLSA"><strong>Spotify</strong></a></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Listen on </strong><a href="https://podcasts.google.com/feed/aHR0cHM6Ly9mZWVkcy5idXp6c3Byb3V0LmNvbS8xMjIwOTYzLnJzcw/episode/QnV6enNwcm91dC01NjEzOTQw?sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiWmoiJq43sAhXbhXIEHc2LBKMQkfYCegQIARAF"><strong>Google Podcasts</strong></a></p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><h2>Episode Highlights</h2><p class="">I've also pulled the best highlights from the podcast for you to listen to here:</p><h2>Clip 1: Being Consistent and Taking small steps</h2><p class="">Q: How can you ensure success in a new business, project or creative pursuit?</p><p class="">A: Build momentum by being consistent and taking small steps toward your goal</p><p class="">That's the lesson both guest Agustin Zavala (<a href="https://twitter.com/biotech_bros?lang=en">Biotech_Bros</a>) and Avthar Sewrathan (@<a href="https://twitter.com/avthars">avthars</a>) uncovered in their journeys as creatives and entrepreneurs.</p><p class="">In this clip from LWA #2, Avthar and Agustin discuss how their past mistakes have taught them the power of consistency and taking actionable steps, as well as why it's important to be in the "Clouds" and "Dirt" simultaneously as a creator and founder.</p><p class="">🎧 <a href="https://avthar.buzzsprout.com/1220963/5596813-being-consistent-and-taking-small-steps">Listen here</a></p><iframe allow="autoplay; fullscreen" scrolling="no" data-image-dimensions="500x210" allowfullscreen="true" src="//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buzzsprout.com%2F1220963%2F5596813-being-consistent-and-taking-small-steps%3Fclient_source%3Dtwitter_card%26player_type%3Dfull_screen&amp;disp